Description: Fragment of neck and oval handle of a pottery transport amphora, gradual curve. Dark surface to inside of neck. Clay near fine, micaceous, red-brown. Red paint on neck, and the inner surface stained black, as part of the neck. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie noted several such stamps in his 1884-5 diary (EES Archive XVII 47).
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1366)
